parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle jerks or hesitates while accelerating
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle may not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bearing can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The bearing fails
causing the vehicle to lose power
jerk
or hesitate while shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random misfires and engine issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The traction control light
stability light
and check engine light illuminate
the vehicle experiences random misfires
and the vehicle may not accelerate to safe speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal goes to the floor
inability to stop the vehicle
warning lights and ABS brake light on the dashboard
random brake failure while driving or reversing on an incline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EBCM can cause the brakes to lose assisted power, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: "Service StabiliTrak" or "Service Brake Assist" warning messages
random brake failure while driving
loss of assisted power while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brakes to lose assisted power, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Random brake failure while driving
loss of assisted power while braking
brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to distractions, safety risks, and inconvenience.
symptoms: Door alarm not sounding
radio staying on and draining the battery
radio volume freezing or becoming unresponsive
overhead light flickering or becoming unresponsive
battery dying without warning
and warning lights illuminating simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radio/infotainment system can cause distractions, battery drain, and inconvenience.
symptoms: Radio staying on and draining the battery
radio volume freezing or becoming unresponsive
touch screen becoming unresponsive
and issues with Bluetooth connectivity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various safety and convenience features to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Warning lights illuminating simultaneously
inability to lock or operate the vehicle
and inability to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle's stability and control systems can cause loss of control, accidents, and safety risks.
symptoms: Vehicle shaking or veering off the road
and loss of control.
